          About the Job
           Our team focuses on the scheduling user experience for outlook clients. We are currently working with big data and building tools and models to extract relevant business information, consolidating a heterogeneous set of data streams from different Outlook clients. We want to build a pipeline that allows us to identify features and areas of investment that have a greater impact on growth and user satisfaction. We are building Machine Learning (ML) techniques to perform social clustering and identify usage patterns correlated to relevant business metrics.
           Your role: You are a hands-on data scientist with strong algorithmic and machine learning background. You welcome the challenge of big data and are proficient in R/Python, C#, social network analysis (SNA) and statistical modeling. You must be self-driven, take initiative and want to work in a dynamic, busy and innovative group. A strong engineer background is a plus.
           Key Tasks and Responsibilities: Work as part of the calendar scheduling team to develop cutting edge methodologies in scheduling Analytics.
           The potential scope of this role is very broad and includes:
           - Working with the Product team to prototype, develop and refine data-driven product metrics and features
           - Tinkering with the data to explore and came up with innovative features and improvements to the engineering/development pipeline.
           - Helping to govern and manage the enormous and complex pipeline of data that we use in our product and decision making
           - Helping to develop the skills of the entire team as data-savvy leaders who ask great questions and make informed decisions
           Qualifications:
           - Master or Bachelor in Statistics/Math/Computer Science or related field
           - 2+ years of relevant programming skills data mining, big data, machine learning, natural language processing, and similar experiences is a plus
           - Experience and proficiency in coding skills in C#
           - Excellent oral and written communication skills and be able to interact effectively with development, operation and business teams in Microsoft
